# Files and comments

## Single responsibility per file

- Prefer **one main type or concern per file** (e.g. one `enum` for layout constants, one factory for court nodes, one `SKScene` subclass for orchestration).
- When a file grows to cover multiple unrelated concerns, **split** into new files in the same module instead of stacking unrelated types in one file.
- **Exceptions**: tiny helpers that only exist to support a single public API may stay colocated if splitting would obscure the API.

```swift
// ❌ Avoid: Playfield metrics + physics masks + all node factories + SKScene in one file.

// ✅ Prefer: Playfield.swift, PhysicsCategory.swift, PongCourtElements.swift, PongScene.swift
```

## Detailed comments

- Add a **short comment above each logical block** (type, extension, `MARK` section, or private helper group) stating **what it does** and **why it exists**, not a restatement of the identifier name.
- For non-obvious math, coordinates, or lifecycle order, **one line** explaining the invariant or call order is enough.
- **Avoid**: noisy comments on every line, repeating the code verbatim, or deleting existing useful comments when editing nearby code.

```swift
// ❌ // set x to 5
// ✅ // Wall center sits at -halfH + thickness/2 so the inner face aligns with the playfield bound.
```
